      <hedline>
        <hl1>Affordable Capri</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Claude M Gruener letter on Adam Begley's May 27 travel article on Graham Green's Capri</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding ''Graham Greene's Capri'' (May 27) by Adam Begley: Having visited Capri some 10 times over the last 20 years, I would like to point out that it is not only for the very rich. There are many places to stay that do not strain the budget, and some have private balconies and terraces with incredible views of the ocean and mountains. Of course, they are not luxurious, but who has time to spend more than a few hours a night in their room anyway?</p>
        <p>Two handy Web sites are www.capritourism.com and www.capri.net. Many lodgings have double rooms for 120 euros or less -- with breakfast and view included.</p>
        <p>Claude M. Gruener  Austin, Tex.</p>
      </block>
